description.plain:
Jamell Maurice Demons (born May 1, 1999), better known by his stage name YNW Melly, is an American rapper, singer, and songwriter who emerged from Gifford, Florida. YNW Melly is also co-founder of rap collective, YNW. His music often draws from his lived experiences, evidenced by his 2017 incarceration for weapons charges. Upon release, he began to gain popularity from his track “Murder On My Mind.” which he wrote while in jail. After the release of the track, he was once again arrested as the song violated his probation, and sent him back to prison.

Melly’s career initially started to take off in 2018 when singles such as “Virtual (Blue Balenciagas)”, “Butter Pecan”, and “772 Love” had begun to gain popularity alongside “Murder on My Mind.”

On August 3, 2018, Melly released his debut mixtape I AM YOU which included his popular single, “Murder on My Mind”. It also included a sequel to the song called “Mind on My Murder”.

After leaving the studio with companions YNW Bortlen, YNW SakChaser, and YNW Juvy, on the night of October 26, 2018, Melly and his friends had been caught in a drive-by-shooting where SakChaser and Juvy were murdered. Melly and Bortlen were the only survivors of the attack.

While working on his sophomore mixtape, after the death of his friends, Melly had gained more attention and began to obtain cosigns from several rappers such as Young Thug, Trippie Redd, and Kodak Black. However, on January 3, 2019, Melly was arrested for possession of marijuana.

On January 18, 2019, while incarcerated, Melly released his sophomore mixtape We All Shine, which included one of his most influential cosign’s, Kanye West who was a feature on the song “Mixed Personalities.”.

Melly was released from jail on January 25, 2019, and released “Gang”, the first day out single that had taken off after the hype around “Mixed Personalities.”

After being released for only a month, on February 13, 2019, Melly turned himself in after a warrant was put out for him and Bortlen connecting to the murders of YNW Sakchaser and YNW Juvy. YNW Melly posted this to his Instagram on February 13:

To all my fans and supporters no I did not get locked up in Washington , but I am turning myself in today I want you guys to know I love you and appreciate every single one of y'all, a couple months ago I lost my two brothers by violence and now the system want to find justice.. unfortunately a lot of rumors and lies are being said but no worries god is with me and my brother @ynw.bortlen and we want y'all to remember it’s a ynw Family I love you @ynwsakchaser1 and @ynwjuvy #freeus

Prior to his incarceration, songs such as “Murder on My Mind” and “Mind on My Murder” had gained traction making their way in the Billboard Hot 100 and gaining RIAA certifications in a matter of months. Speculations made people believe that the songs were related to the murders, however, they were soon put to rest due to the time of the recordings being almost two years prior to the shootings.

After spending months incarcerated, on November 22, 2019, he released his debut studio album, Melly vs. Melvin featuring his 9lokkNine-assisted “223’s”.

After the rise of COVID-19 disease in 2020, on April 3, Melly had tested positive for the virus while awaiting trial. After being infected, Melly’s lawyers tried to play this to his advantage and requested a medical release as conditions can worsen in the jail environment. Melly was denied release on April 17 and conditions have been said to worsen since.

After the release of fellow Floridian rapper Kodak Black, Melly’s team had taken advantage and released “Thugged Out” to keep Melly’s name alive in the industry. They carried on releasing singles throughout the year with artists such as Quuen Naija and Hotboii.

Again, while still awaiting trial, on August 13, 2021, he released his sophomore studio album, Just A Matter of Slime, featuring his highly anticipated Lil Uzi Vert-assisted “Mind of Melvin”.

After prosecutors had claimed they had a confession of Melly admitting to the murders, on November 1, Melly’s lawyers came out and denied the claims and said that Melly was just rapping a song titled “4:30 AM” by Kevin Gates. Soon after, on November 30, Melly’s trial had been set for March 7, 2022.

description.plain:
“Murder on My Mind” is YNW Melly’s breakout song. It depicts a dark, upsetting story of Melly shooting a close friend and holding him in his arms as he slowly lost consciousness and died. Melly also mentions his previous jail time served for gun charges and drug possession. The shooting he refers to in this song happened in 2016 or earlier.

In an interview with HotNewHipHop, Melly described how he had written this after being charged with three counts of aggravated assault with a deadly weapon and one count of discharging a firearm in public and had been locked up for a year. In the interview he said how all 240 inmates and the staff enjoyed his song and that’s how he knew it’d be a hit.

Following the release of the track on Soundcloud in 2017, the track’s lyrics supposedly violated Melly’s probation for his prior charge; sending him back to prison.

Over a year after the release of the audio, Melly released the official music video directed by the popular director Gabriel Hart. The video gave a demonic and creepy vibe while vividly showing the fictional crime scene Melly describes.

A month after the release of the video, the song started gaining traction hence Melly released “Mischief on My Mind”, a clean, radio-edited version of “Murder on My Mind”.

“Murder on My Mind” was soon followed up by a sequel, “Mind on My Murder,” which depicts the same events of this song from the victim’s perspective. It is subsequent to the album’s tracklisting.

A remix of the track featuring late Chicago rapper Juice WRLD was released on March 13, 2020, with Juice WRLD adding his two cents on the breakup and his own struggles with Hennessy.

description.plain:
On the remix of his November 2019 standout track, “Suicidal”, YNW Melly enlists the late Juice WRLD for a song about failed relationships.

The track was first previewed on Melly’s Instagram on December 8, 2019, the same morning Juice’s tragic death due to drug overdose occurred. The track was officially announced on March 11, 2020, two days before its release.

This marks the second collaboration between the two, as they both featured on Trippie Redd’s November 2019 track, “6 Kiss”. The track also marks Juice’s third posthumous feature, following Eminem’s 2020 “Godzilla“ and G Herbo’s 2020 “PTSD“.

description.plain:
In the song “Virtual (Blue Balenciagas)”, YNW Melly raps about a detailed scene of a murder, his selection of firearms, and his unique style of wearing Blue Balenciagas leading to having a rival gang members blood on his shoes.

Balenciaga, is a high-end, luxury/designer brand originating from Spain. Melly wears Blue Balenciagas with blood on them to contrast the colors, mocking the Crip Gang members as it portrays the blood of a deceased member, this is done due to his affiliation with the rival Blood Gang which he has spoken about in songs such as “Adam Sandler”, Young Grizzley World", and “Bang Bang”.

The unique Trap beat was provided by EY3ZLOWBEATZ. It became one of his most successful tracks then being placed on YNW Melly’s debut mixtape, “I AM YOU” which was released on August 3, 2018.

The official music video was filmed by St. Petersburg native cameraman, DrewFilmedIt. It shows YNW Melly dancing with guns and performing robberies with his gang. In the music video, they are wearing masks similar to the nun masks from the 2010 heist movie called “The Town”. The idea of the music video was inspired by the film as there are very similar themes of crime between the movie and the music video.

Melly wears Blue Balenciagas with blood on them to contrast the colors, mocking the Crip Gang members as it portrays the blood of a deceased member, this is done due to his affiliation with the rival Blood Gang which he has spoken about in songs such as “Adam Sandler”, Young Grizzley World", and “Bang Bang”.

The unique Trap beat was provided by EY3ZLOWBEATZ. It became one of his most successful tracks then being placed on YNW Melly’s debut mixtape, “I AM YOU” which was released on August 3, 2018.

The official music video was filmed by St. Petersburg native cameraman, DrewFilmedIt. It shows YNW Melly dancing with guns and performing robberies with his gang. In the music video, they are wearing masks similar to the nun masks from the 2010 heist movie called “The Town”. The idea of the music video was inspired by the film as there are very similar themes of crime between the movie and the music video.

The track was previewed on Instagram on January 17, 2019, where Melly called while being incarcerated in Lee County Jail after being arrested for possession of marijuana. “Two Face” is about the two most known personalities of YNW Melly, however, four have been mentioned: Melly, Melvin, Marcus and Marvin. YNW Melly is known to have up to six different personas. Melly and Melvin have very different personality traits; Melly has the softer and nicer persona, whilst Melvin has more hard hitting and thug-like persona. These two personas of YNW Melly have been insinuated about in his song “Mixed Personalities”, which features veteran rapper Kanye West. On “Mixed Personalities”, Kanye and Melly/Melvin repeat that they have “mixed personalities” throughout the song’s chorus. Melly also stated in his Genius interview on Verified for “Murder On My Mind”, that Melvin’s the meaner personality, the one who wakes up with “that murder on his mind”.

YNW Melly also mentioned Marcus. In an interview, Melly has said that Marcus has been to be Melly when he’s doing “normal nigga shit” in the past. When the interviewer asked about his other personalities, he said “I can’t tell you, they won’t let me”.

In “Na Na Na Boo Boo,” YNW Melly channels his inner kid by repeatedly using the childish playground taunt that the rapper named his song after. The song was originally released on September 3, 2018, but was re-released on March 26, 2021, after going viral on TikTok. Similar to what happened with “223s” which was re-released after going TikTok viral.

Melly raps about his early lifestyle, growing up in a bad neighborhood having to do illegal activities to get money, while Kodak talks about his time in prison and about various assaults.
